50|$|Considering <b>antenna</b> <b>diversity,</b> in many systems {{additional}} antennas may {{be expensive}} or impractical at the remote or {{even at the}} base station. In these cases, transmit diversity {{can be used to}} provide diversity benefit at a receiver with multiple transmit antennas only. With transmit diversity, multiple antennas transmit delayed versions of a signal, creating frequency-selective fading, which is equalized at the receiver to provide diversity gain.|$|E
