5000|$|DiBcom is a French fabless {{semiconductor}} {{company that}} designs chipsets for low-power mobile TV and radio reception. Its chipsets are compliant {{with the current}} worldwide Digital Video Broadcasting standards DVB-T, DVB-T2, DVB-H, DVB-SH, with ATSC-M/H, ISDB-T (1seg and Full-SEG), CMMB and with DAB, DAB+, DMB in multistandard programmable platforms. It specializes in <b>antenna</b> <b>diversity</b> demodulator chipsets with a built-in tuner to minimize component count.|$|E
5000|$|Diversity techniques: To {{improve the}} quality of the {{received}} signal, often two receiving antennas are used, placed at a distance equal to an odd multiple of a quarter of the corresponding wavelength. For 900 MHz, this wavelength is 30 cm. This technique, known as <b>antenna</b> <b>diversity</b> or space diversity, avoids interruption caused by path fading. The antennas can be spaced horizontally or vertically. Horizontal spacing requires more complex installation, but brings better performance.|$|E
